  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this project, entitled &quot;Meaning-Centered Psychotherapy Training for Cancer
      Care Providers,&quot; is to develop a multi-modal training program in Meaning-Centered
      Psychotherapy (MCP) for multidisciplinary cancer care clinicians who provide psycho-oncology
      and psychosocial palliative care services for cancer patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
